# Drain the capture outbox

## Step

Resolved when: (1) the writer still POSTing capture deltas to a 404 route
is identified and fixed (the review caught a live `POST 404 ... outboxed`
at 10:00:42 on 2026-07-17); (2) the `~/.joelclaw/outbox/` backlog —
14,798 files, 71.38 GB, oldest 2026-06-08 — has a safe disposition
executed: analyzed for what's replayable vs already-captured-elsewhere vs
junk, deduped, replayed in a rate-limited way that cannot hammer live
ingestion or double-index runs, with raw deletion only after a step-level
check-in with steering; and (3) a size/age alarm on the outbox is wired
into an existing watch surface (telemetry watch or observer
self-maintenance) so a silent pile-up can never reach 71 GB again.
Analysis and the replay PLAN come first; execution of the drain follows
steering review of that plan. Evidence:
[periphery survey](../memory-system-review/periphery-survey.svx)
"Run/session archive and capture state" + flag #4.

## Result (2026-07-17)

Implementation and the reviewed replay plan are ready. The live gateway restart, supervised replay canary, backlog drain, and observer alarm deployment still belong to steering; this step stays open until those receipts exist.

### Root cause and fix

The 10:00:42 PDT failure was the embedded **gateway Pi session**, not Claude
or Codex. `~/.joelclaw/capture.log` named session
`019f6f5c-10e9-74aa-8a46-ea3ecb012894`; its source transcript is
`~/.joelclaw/sessions/gateway/2026-07-17T09-15-32-458Z_019f6f5c-10e9-74aa-8a46-ea3ecb012894.jsonl`.
The gateway LaunchAgent/start script did not export `JOELCLAW_CENTRAL_URL`,
and process readback confirmed it was absent. The Pi extension therefore used
its dead `http://localhost:3000` fallback. Read-only probes returned 404 from
`http://localhost:3000/api/runs/health` and 200 from the actual worker at
`http://127.0.0.1:3111/api/runs/health`. Other Pi sessions inherited a good
`:3111` URL, which explains successful captures seconds apart.

Fixed all three writer defaults to `http://127.0.0.1:3111`:

- `packages/pi-extensions/memory-capture/index.ts`
- `scripts/joelclaw-capture-session.ts`
- `scripts/joelclaw-capture-codex-session.js`

Their log writers now use append-only `appendFileSync`; the old read-whole-log
then rewrite pattern lost evidence when concurrent sessions wrote the same log.

**Steering bounce:** after applying/committing this patch, run
`joelclaw gateway restart` so the embedded gateway Pi reloads the extension.
Existing interactive Pi sessions that loaded the old extension need a Pi
restart or extension reload. Claude/Codex launch their capture scripts per Stop
hook, so the code fallback changes apply on the next hook invocation; their
current hook configs already inject the working Flagg `:3111` URL. The worker
does not need a restart for this client-only fix.

