The reviewed plan is `/tmp/capture-outbox-plan.json`; it contains no transcript
text, only paths, hashes, sizes, grouping, and disposition.

### Replay plan — built, not executed

`scripts/replay-capture-outbox.ts` is dry-run/plan mode by default. It:

1. validates every body and groups by runtime + conversation + parent run;
2. keeps only maximal deltas, skipping exact copies and strict prefixes;
3. checks `runs_dev` plus raw `jsonl_path` siblings before each replay;
4. skips captured supersets and deterministically trims captured prefixes,
   reparenting the suffix to the captured run;
5. binds every reviewed catalog row to the live realpath, mtime, size, envelope,
   source-body SHA, and JSONL SHA before any query or POST;
6. verifies every raw captured sibling against its indexed `jsonl_sha256`
   before using it to cover or trim a prefix;
7. uses `run_id + source-body SHA + replay-JSONL SHA` as the dedupe key;
8. writes an append-only `inflight → accepted → indexed` checkpoint and never
   automatically resends an inflight, accepted, or failed item that has not
   indexed; failed retries require `--retry-failed-run <run-id>` after review;
9. stops on SHA conflict, non-2xx, missing index confirmation, SIGINT/SIGTERM,
   or the kill file `~/.joelclaw/capture-outbox.STOP`;
10. paginates captured-sibling search, rate-limits to one request/second, 25
   per batch, 30 seconds between batches, 64 MiB per file, and 256 MiB per
   batch by default;
11. never imports deletion/move operations. Source cleanup remains a separate,
   steering-approved phase after raw + Typesense + event receipts agree.

First supervised canary after the gateway bounce:

```bash
bun scripts/replay-capture-outbox.ts \
  --run --execute \
  --catalog /tmp/capture-outbox-plan.json \
  --max-files 5 \
  --max-batch-bytes 10485760 \
  --batch-size 5 \
  --rate-ms 1000
```

Review `/tmp/capture-outbox-replay-receipt.json` and the append-only
`~/.joelclaw/capture-outbox-replay-checkpoint.jsonl` before raising the batch.
Do not delete source files after HTTP 202; wait for the script's exact
Typesense SHA readback.

### Alarm implementation

The alarm is committed in the sibling `joelclaw-observer` repo at `01b81cba`.
Its scheduled self-maintenance runner already reads Flagg state and turns
warnings into the observer noise bar. It counts/stats filenames only; it never
reads payload bodies. Warning thresholds: 25 files, 256 MiB, or oldest age 60
minutes. The warning carries a `critical` detail bit at 100 files, 1 GiB, or six
hours. Missing/empty is green; unreadable is warning. The focused observer suite
passes 88 tests. Release promotion is still outstanding.

